    • Method Detail

      • awaitTermination

        boolean awaitTermination(long timeout,
                         TimeUnit unit)
                  throws InterruptedException
        Blocks until all tasks have completed execution after a close request, or the timeout occurs, or the current thread is interrupted, whichever happens first.
        Parameters:
        timeout - the maximum time to wait
        unit - the time unit of the timeout argument
        Returns:
        true if this client terminated and false if the timeout elapsed before termination
        Throws:
        InterruptedException - if interrupted while waiting

      • broadcast

        MmsFuture<Void> broadcast(BroadcastMessage message)
        Asynchronously broadcasts the specified message. No guarantees are made to the delivery of the specified message. The future returned can be used to determine when the messages has been received by the MMS server.
        Parameters:
        message - the message to broadcast
        Returns:
        a future that can be used to determine when the broadcast messages is received by the MMS server
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if the specified message is null
        MmsConnectionClosedException - if the connection has been permanently closed
        See Also:
        withBroadcast(BroadcastMessage)

      • broadcastListen

        <T extends BroadcastMessage> BroadcastSubscription broadcastListen(Class<T> messageType,
                                                                   BroadcastListener<T> consumer)
        Subscribes to the the specified type of broadcast messages.
        Type Parameters:
        T - the type of broadcast message
        Parameters:
        messageType - the type of broadcast message to listen for
        consumer - the consumer that will be invoked for each broadcast message that is received
        Returns:
        a subscription that can be used to stop listening for broadcasts of the specified type
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if the message type or consumer is null
        MmsConnectionClosedException - if the connection has been permanently closed

      • broadcastListen

        <T extends BroadcastMessage> BroadcastSubscription broadcastListen(Class<T> messageType,
                                                                   BroadcastListener<T> consumer,
                                                                   Area area)
        Subscribes to the the specified type of broadcast messages in the specified area.
        Type Parameters:
        T - the type of broadcast
        Parameters:
        messageType - the type of message to listen for
        consumer - the consumer of messages
        area - the area for which the broadcast will be visible to other actors. The area is not relative to the current position of the client.
        Returns:
        a subscription that can be used to stop listening for broadcasts of the specified type
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if the message type, consumer or area is null
        MmsConnectionClosedException - if the connection has been permanently closed

      • close

        void close()
        Asynchronously shutdowns this client. use awaitTermination(long, TimeUnit) to await complete termination (acknowledgment by the remote side).

      • endpointRegister

        EndpointRegistration endpointRegister(EndpointImplementation implementation)
        Registers the specified endpoint with the maritime cloud. If a client is closed via close() the server will automatically deregister all endpoints.
        Parameters:
        implementation - the endpoint implementation
        Returns:
        an endpoint registration object
        Throws:
        MmsConnectionClosedException - if the connection has been permanently closed
